CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 7, 1956, pg. 3 reads: "Cute 'Honeybunnies' Paraded... and captured the hears of everyone at the fashion show at A. Leo Weil School. Wearing perky spring outfits with sparkling smiles on their faces, some came out in pairs, as a single, or in one instance, as a trio.  Left to right:...Janice, Deborah and Brenda Jordan..."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Janice Jordan, Deborah Jordan modeling short sleeved jacket, and Brenda Jordan, standing on stage in A. Leo Weil School for Easter fashion show
